See: Description

Editor Module 
Package Description
org.netbeans.modules.editor  
org.netbeans.modules.editor.options  

The editor functionality are mainly implementations of the Swing Text package APIs plus extension features such as Syntax Coloring, Code Completion, Word Matching, Abbreviations or Macros.

The editor consists of a library part (located under editor/lib and described in a separate arch document) and the module part (under src subfolder) that depends on NetBeans APIs specified in this document.

  • May 26 '08 Deprecating kit class related API in NbEditorDocument

    The use of editor kit implementation class for identifying the type of a document has been deprecated in favor of mime types and MimeLookup. This change deprecates API methods and construction in BaseDocument that accept editor kit implementation class and adds their equivalents accepting EditorKit.

    Deprecated: NbEditorDocument(Class)

    Added: NbEditorDocument(EditorKit)

  • May 21 '08 Editor Actions can be supplied in 'Actions' folder

    The editor actions (ie. actions that are installed in JEditorPanes for Netbeans editors) can now be registered in XML layers under the Actions subfolder. For example adding an action to the java editor can be achieved by adding .instance file to Editors/text/x-java/Actions folder.

  • Jun 16 '07 Change of attribute name for SideBar instances to location

    The position of SideBar instances (East etc.) used to be given by the position attribute. Since that clashes with folder ordering, this attribute was deprecated in favor of location. The old attribute is still read as a backup.

Editor defines APIs and SPIs both by
  • Providing java classes in public packages for further reuse.
    Most of the classes were created spontaneously (several years ago) without fulfilling of the rules imposed on APIs and SPIs at the present time.
    There is an ongoing work to revisit the existing classes and create stable APIs and SPIs (and possibly extract functionality into a submodule where appropriate). However this is a long-term task spanning several promotions.
  • Being sensitive to content of certain directories in xml layer.
